Q1. What is the purpose of the try statement?
Ans. A try statement is used to catch exceptions that might be thrown as your program 
executes. You should use a try statement whenever you use a statement that might throw an 
exception That way, your program won't crash if the exception occurs. The statements that 
might throw an exception within a try block.

Q2. What are the two most popular try statement variations?
Ans. The most popular try statement  variations are:
i) try_catch ii) try-catch-finally

Q3. What is the purpose of the raise statement?
Ans. Purpose of  the raise  statement is raising some exception depending on scenario.

Q4. What does the assert statement do, and what other statement is it like?
Ans. assert statement is used to do some task depending on the some conditiona and if 
the  codition isn't  satisfied then it generates some exception.
      The statement look like if.
Q5. What is the purpose of the with/as argument, and what other statement is it like?
Ans. with statement in Python is used in exception handling to make the code cleaner and 
much more readable. It simplifies the management of common resources like file streams. As
statement is used to give a shorted name to an identifier.
        The statements looks like typedef of C.
